Package org.joml

Class Matrix3x2fStack

java.lang.Object
org.joml.Matrix3x2f
org.joml.Matrix3x2fStack
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, Matrix3x2fc
public class Matrix3x2fStack
extends Matrix3x2f
A stack of many Matrix3x2f instances. This resembles the matrix stack known from legacy OpenGL.

This Matrix3x2fStack class inherits from Matrix3x2f, so the current/top matrix is always the Matrix3x2fStack/Matrix3x2f itself. This affects all operations in Matrix3x2f that take another Matrix3x2f as parameter. If a Matrix3x2fStack is used as argument to those methods, the effective argument will always be the current matrix of the matrix stack.

Author:
Kai Burjack

  • Constructor Details

    • Matrix3x2fStack

      public Matrix3x2fStack​(int stackSize)
      Create a new Matrix3x2fStack of the given size.

      Initially the stack pointer is at zero and the current matrix is set to identity.

      Parameters:
      stackSize - the size of the stack. This must be at least 1, in which case the Matrix3x2fStack simply only consists of this Matrix3x2f

    • Matrix3x2fStack

      public Matrix3x2fStack()
      Do not invoke manually! Only meant for serialization.

      Invoking this constructor from client code will result in an inconsistent state of the created Matrix3x2fStack instance.
